--- Part 3: KEY TEST ---
  Does rank(i_*) = 1 whenever b3(T\v) = 1?
  YES! rank(i_*) = 1 for ALL 18 bad vertex cases
  This means: when b3(T\v) = 1, H_3(T,T\v) = 1 - 1 = 0
  And: b3(T) = rank(i_*) + H_3^rel = 1 + 0 = 1. QED!

  PROOF IMPLICATION:
  For any vertex v of a beta_3=1 tournament T:
    - If b3(T\v) = 0: H_3^rel = 1, rank(i_*) = 0. b3(T) = 0 + 1 = 1.
    - If b3(T\v) = 1: H_3^rel = 0, rank(i_*) = 1. b3(T) = 1 + 0 = 1.
  Either way, b3(T) = 1. No good vertex needed!

